# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Frontend Environment Variables
# Copy to .env.local for local development. Never commit .env.local.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# URL of the FastAPI backend (used by the API service client).
# Leave empty (default) in development — the Vite proxy at /api/* forwards
# requests to the backend, so both the PC and mobile phone only need to reach
# the Vite dev server. Only set this when running outside of Vite
# (e.g. Storybook, tests, or production builds).
# VITE_API_URL=http://localhost:8000

# ── Mobile Upload / QR-Code ───────────────────────────────────────────────────
# No extra config needed for the QR-Code mobile flow!
# The QR code uses window.location.origin automatically.
#
# To test with your phone on the local network:
#   1. docker-compose up --build  (Vite now listens on 0.0.0.0:5173)
#   2. Find your PC's local IP:  ipconfig  (Windows) / ip a  (Linux/macOS)
#   3. Open http://<YOUR-LOCAL-IP>:5173 in your PC browser
#   4. Click "Mit dem Handy scannen" — the QR code will contain your local IP
#   5. Phone scans → both page and API go through the Vite proxy → no CORS
#
# In production (resovva.de) this works out of the box, no changes needed.

# Stripe public key (used for client-side checkout redirect)
VITE_STRIPE_PUBLIC_KEY=pk_test_your_key_here
